{
  "message": "fix(store): preserve destination TTL during PFMERGE (Redis parity)\n\nPFMERGE was clearing the destination key's TTL by always inserting with\nexpires_at_ms=None. Redis preserves the existing TTL when modifying a key\nin-place during merge. Now captures the existing TTL before the merge and\ncarries it forward to the new entry.\n\nAdded 9 conformance tests verifying TTL preservation: set TTL on dest,\nmerge source into it, verify TTL survives; also verify new dest gets no TTL.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
